RODIMUS gave WHEELIE a sour look as he reluctantly leaned back on the
bed he was on, realizing he was not going to the get the support that
he wanted. "Fine." he said as looked at UNUS and WHEELIE.

UNUS was looking thoughtful as he watched RODIMUS and WHEELIE, "I
don't know much about Magmatron, except that he had Saberback build
us." His words were careful as if he were dipping back as far into his
memory as he could go.

If there was little known about Magmatron, there was even less known
about Saberback. Some called him a wizard others called him a
scientist, but as to where he came from or what his true goals were
none knew. He has served with MAGMATRON for as far back as anyone
could remember. Rarely seen in the past he was elusive, secretive and
as wicked as they came.

The nurse looked at UNUS and WHEELIE, "Perhaps we should let this one
rest for a while. " She glanced back at RODIMUS.

UNUS nodded, "Of course." He said as he looked at WHEELIE, "Perhaps we
should give him more time to recover." His words bordering somewhere
between a command and a suggestion.

(TAG)
